'''DocHub''' is an online [[Portable Document Format|PDF]] editor and document signing platform.<ref>{{Cite web|title = DocHub|url = http://www.dochub.com|website = DocHub|accessdate = 2015-11-18}}</ref> DocHub lets users add text, draw, add signatures and make document templates.<ref>{{Cite web|title = 8 free apps that pump up Google Drive|url = http://www.infoworld.com/article/2948125/cloud-storage/8-free-apps-pump-up-google-drive.html#slide5|website = InfoWorld|accessdate = 2015-11-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = 5 helpful Chromebook tools for marking up documents, photos, and web pages|url = http://www.pcworld.com/article/2998263/chromebooks/5-helpful-chromebook-tools-for-marking-up-documents-photos-and-web-pages.html#slide3}}</ref> DocHub can [[wikt:integration|integrate]] with [[Dropbox (service)|Dropbox]], [[Google Drive]], [[Gmail]] and [[Box (company)|Box]] accounts.
== Users == As of April 2017, DocHub has at least 18.1 million registered users.<ref>{{Cite web|title = About {{!}} DocHub|url = https://dochub.com/about|website = DocHub|accessdate = 2015-11-18|registration = }}</ref> Over 68 million documents have been created on DocHub.<ref>{{Cite web|title = About {{!}} DocHub|url = http://www.dochub.com/about|website = DocHub|accessdate = 2015-11-18}}</ref>
